{
  "id": "MGASA-2014-0315",
  "summary": "Updated polarssl packages fix security vulnerability",
  "details": "A flaw was discovered in PolarSSL, a lightweight crypto and SSL/TLS library,\nwhich can be exploited by a remote unauthenticated attacker to mount a denial\nof service against PolarSSL servers that offer GCM ciphersuites. Potentially\nclients are affected too if a malicious server decides to execute the denial\nof service attack against its clients (CVE-2014-4911).\n\nThe pdns package has been rebuilt against the updated polarssl library.\n",
